'''斯坦福書店'''（{{lang-en|Stanfords}}）是[[英國|英國]][[倫敦|倫敦]]的一家專門經營[[地圖|地圖]]和[[遊記|旅行圖書]]的書店，由{{link-en|愛德華·斯坦福|Edward Stanford}}創業於1853年<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/10/13/iconic-london-travel-bookshop-stanfords-is-set-to-move-after-117-years-in-covent-garden-8034469/|title=Stanfords travel bookshop is set to move after 117 years in Covent Garden|last=Garcia|first=Francisco|date=2018-10-13|work=Metro|access-date=2018-10-26|language=en-GB|archive-date=2021-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210823145939/https://metro.co.uk/2018/10/13/iconic-london-travel-bookshop-stanfords-is-set-to-move-after-117-years-in-covent-garden-8034469/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。斯坦福書店收集了世界最大規模的地圖、[[地球儀|地球儀]]和海圖<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.edumaritime.net/maritime-store/stanfords-maritime-books-products|title=Maritime Charts, Books & Official Publications|access-date=2021-08-23|language=en-GB|archive-date=2020-12-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201222085017/https://www.edumaritime.net/maritime-store/stanfords-maritime-books-products|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/travel/comment/stanfords-london-cartographers/|title=Stanfords to close Long Acre store, launchpad for explorers young and old, after 117 years|last=Dickinson|first=Greg|date=2018-10-11|work=The Telegraph|access-date=2018-10-26|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235|archive-date=2021-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210823152127/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/travel/comment/stanfords-london-cartographers/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。斯坦福書店亦為[[英國陸軍|英國陸軍]]和[[占士邦|占士邦]]電影提供製圖服務。

== 歷史 ==
斯坦福書店在其開業時是倫敦唯一的地圖製作商，並委託約翰·博爾頓擔任內部[[地圖學|製圖師]]<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thetravel.com/worlds-largest-map-shop-relocating-iconic-location-after-117-years/|title=World's Largest Map Shop Will Be Relocated From Its Iconic Location After 117 Years|last=Lugris|first=Mark|date=2018-10-15|work=TheTravel|access-date=2018-10-26|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210823145923/https://www.thetravel.com/worlds-largest-map-shop-relocating-iconic-location-after-117-years/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。斯坦福書店的創業期正值全球探險和殖民主義的高峰期，因此當時英國對地圖產品有旺盛需求。斯坦福書店迅速擴張至[[查令十字|查令十字]]7號和8號，並在三一宮（Trinity Place）購地用於印刷<ref name="history" />。1901年1月，斯坦福書店完全搬遷至倫敦市中心[[科文特花园|科文特花园]]的[[朗埃克|朗埃克]]。該地曾是書店印刷部門的所在地<ref name=":0" /><ref name="history">{{cite web|title=Stanfords – A Brief History|publisher=Stanfords|url=http://www.stanfords.co.uk/our-history|access-date=2017-07-17|archive-date=2021-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210823150147/https://www.stanfords.co.uk/our-history|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

1941年，斯坦福書店被一個燃燒彈擊中。但因書店上層有大量[[英國地形測量局|地形測量局]]地圖緊密堆疊，制止了大火蔓延，書店得以倖存<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/9854eb12-d2da-11e8-a9f2-7574db66bcd5|title=Short cuts: venerable travel bookshop Stanfords on the move|last=Robbins|first=Tom|date=2018-10-19|website=Financial Times|language=en-GB|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210823145939/https://www.ft.com/content/9854eb12-d2da-11e8-a9f2-7574db66bcd5|archive-date=2021-08-23|access-date=2018-10-26|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

在開業150週年紀念之際，斯坦福書店在一層張貼了一張[[國家地理學會|國家地理]]世界地圖，其它樓層則張貼了喜馬拉雅山和倫敦的地圖<ref name="history" />。這些地圖耗資4萬英鎊<ref>Mason, M. (2013). ''Walk the Lines: The London Underground, Overground''. London: Arrow Books. {{ISBN|978-0-099-55793-7}}</ref>。1997年，斯坦福書店在[[布里斯托爾|布里斯托爾]]開業了第二家商店<ref name="bristol store">{{cite web|title=Bristol Store|publisher=Stanfords|url=http://www.stanfords.co.uk/bristol-store|access-date=2017-07-17|archive-date=2021-06-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210621150950/https://www.stanfords.co.uk/bristol-store|dead-url=no}}</ref>。斯坦福書店在[[曼徹斯特|曼徹斯特]]亦有分支機構，提供商業用途的地圖製作，例如規劃用的大比例尺地圖。2018年，斯坦福書店在科文特花园的Mercer Walk7號開設新店。2019年1月，斯坦福書店關閉了在朗埃克的舊址<ref>{{cite web |last1=Turner |first1=Sarah |title=Stanfords, The World's Most Famous Map And Travel Bookshop, Is On The Move |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/sarahturner/2019/01/28/stanfords-the-worlds-most-famous-map-and-travel-bookshop-is-on-the-move/#7775767ccc50 |work=Forbes |access-date=2019-07-17 |archive-date=2020-11-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108001009/https://www.forbes.com/sites/sarahturner/2019/01/28/stanfords-the-worlds-most-famous-map-and-travel-bookshop-is-on-the-move/#7775767ccc50 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first=Will |last=Smale |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-50069476 |title=The map store boss who took the long route |work=BBC News |date=2019-10-21 |accessdate=2021-08-23 |archive-date=2021-08-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210823151417/https://www.bbc.com/news/business-50069476 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 著名客戶 ==
斯坦福書店有「探險者的必備第一站」之稱，其服務過的著名客戶包括[[戴维·利文斯通|戴维·利文斯通]]、[[罗伯特·斯科特|罗伯特·斯科特]]、[[歐內斯特·沙克爾頓|歐內斯特·沙克爾頓]]、[[弗羅倫斯·南丁格爾|弗羅倫斯·南丁格爾]]、{{link-en|拉努夫·費因斯|Ranulph Fiennes}}、[[比爾·布萊森|比爾·布萊森]]和[[迈克尔·帕林|迈克尔·帕林]]<ref name="history" />。斯坦福書店還提供了{{link-en|艾米·約翰遜|Amy Johnson}}獨自飛往澳洲的航圖<ref name=":1" />。在小說中，[[柯南·道爾|柯南·道爾]]在《[[巴斯克維爾的獵犬|巴斯克維爾的獵犬]]》記載[[夏洛克·福爾摩斯|夏洛克·福爾摩斯]]前往斯坦福書店購買[[達特穆爾|達特穆爾]]的地圖<ref name="sb">{{cite news|title=The Hound of Baskervilles|url=https://www.arthur-conan-doyle.com/index.php?title=The_Hound_of_the_Baskervilles/|access-date=2020-12-13|work=www.arthur-conan-doyle.com}}{{Dead link}}</ref>。

